snippet.textDisplay:
What's the difference in the philosophy of Sufis  and Prophets?  
1) Prophets had such faith in God and such  courage that they were able to take up arms when faced with evil enemies. 
2) Prophets took very good care of their own health and they did not seek the help of alcohol, drugs or dance to soothe their strained nerves or fix their broken hearts. 
3)Prophets lived among their families and enemies in town, often dealing with extremely antagonistic relatives and neighbors. 
4)Prophets believed that understanding and teaching others was important even if no one understood or agreed with them. 
I'M SAYING THIS ONLY TO REMIND MYSELF THAT THE TIME FOR JHOOM JHOOM IS OVER AND I MUST PROTEST OUTSIDE THE COMFORT OF MY HOME TO ACHIEVE FREEDOM.
